<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>LE Handoff Package — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Investigative Findings &amp; Recommended Actions</div>
    <h1>Law Enforcement<br/>Handoff Package</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Independent on-chain trace and identified-wallet record prepared for
      handoff to the assigned investigator or supervising agency.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared On Behalf Of</dt>
      <dd>{{ victim.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ victim.citizenship or "Citizenship not on record" }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>{{ investigator.email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Brief Identifier</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ brief_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Stolen Value (Initial)</dt>
      <dd>USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}<span class="secondary">{{ asset.symbol }} on {{ primary_chain | default("Ethereum") }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Asset Issuer</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer.name }}{% if issuer.jurisdiction %}<span class="secondary">{{ issuer.jurisdiction }}</span>{% endif %}</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<div class="summary-box">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }} at the time of
    transaction) was removed without authorization from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet
    {% if victim.citizenship %}(citizen of {{ victim.citizenship }}){% endif %}.
    The token is issued by {{ issuer.name }}{% if issuer.jurisdiction %},
    a {{ issuer.jurisdiction }} entity{% endif %}.
    {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
    Its underlying strategy is operated by {{ issuer.secondary_party }}
    ({{ issuer.secondary_role }}).
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    The position was promptly forwarded by the perpetrator to a secondary
    wallet at <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>, where
    {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers have been
    observed as of {{ verified_at }} UTC.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    The asset's issuer-level controls remain the only available
    mechanism by which redemption can be paused. We recommend that
    a preservation request be issued to {{ issuer.short_name }} as a
    matter of priority.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>2. Victim Information</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Full name:</dt>           <dd>{{ victim.name }}</dd>
  {% if victim.citizenship %}<dt>Citizenship:</dt><dd>{{ victim.citizenship }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.address %}<dt>Residential address:</dt><dd>{{ victim.address }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.email %}<dt>Email:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.email }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
  <dt>Affected wallet:</dt>     <dd class="mono">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
  {% if victim.legal_counsel %}
  <dt>Legal counsel:</dt><dd>{{ victim.legal_counsel }}{% if victim.legal_counsel_email %} &lt;{{ victim.legal_counsel_email }}&gt;{% endif %}</dd>
  {% endif %}
</dl>

{% if victim.incident_summary %}
<h3>Victim's account of the incident</h3>
<p>{{ victim.incident_summary }}</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Timeline of Events (UTC)</h2>
<div class="timeline">
  <div class="timeline-event theft">
    <time>{{ theft_event.timestamp_human }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    <strong>Initial theft.</strong> {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} transferred
    from victim wallet <span class="mono">{{ theft_event.from_address }}</span>
    to perpetrator wallet <span class="mono">{{ theft_event.to_address }}</span>.
    Tx: <span class="mono"><a href="{{ theft_event.explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.tx_hash }}</a></span>
  </div>
  {% for hop in hops %}
  <div class="timeline-event transfer">
    <time>{{ hop.timestamp_human }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    <strong>Hop {{ loop.index }}.</strong>
    {{ hop.amount_human }} {{ hop.symbol }} transferred from
    <span class="mono">{{ hop.from_address }}</span>
    to <span class="mono">{{ hop.to_address }}</span>.
    Tx: <span class="mono"><a href="{{ hop.explorer_url }}">{{ hop.tx_hash }}</a></span>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
  <div class="timeline-event current">
    <time>{{ verified_at }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    <strong>Current state.</strong> Position remains in
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>.
    {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers of the stolen asset observed
    since receipt.
  </div>
</div>

{% if flow_svg %}
<h2>3.1 Fund Flow Diagram</h2>
<div class="flow-diagram" data-case="{{ case_id }}">
  {{ flow_svg|safe }}
  <div class="flow-caption">
    Solid arrows indicate observed on-chain transfers; edge labels show the
    USD-denominated value at the time of transfer with line thickness
    scaled logarithmically to value. Each node represents one address;
    hover-state metadata, when available, names the controlling entity.
    <div class="flow-legend">
      <span class="swatch victim">Victim wallet</span>
      <span class="swatch exchange">Labeled exchange</span>
      <span class="swatch mixer">Mixer (terminal)</span>
      <span class="swatch bridge">Bridge (terminal)</span>
      <span class="swatch contract">DeFi contract</span>
      <span class="swatch wallet">Unlabeled wallet</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Stolen Asset Details</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Asset symbol</th>           <td>{{ asset.symbol }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Token contract address</th> <td class="mono">{{ asset.contract }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Issuer (legal entity)</th>  <td>{{ asset.issuer }}</td></tr>
  {% if issuer.jurisdiction %}<tr><th>Issuer jurisdiction</th><td>{{ issuer.jurisdiction }}</td></tr>{% endif %}
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}<tr><th>Underlying strategy operator</th><td>{{ issuer.secondary_party }} ({{ issuer.secondary_role }})</td></tr>{% endif %}
  <tr><th>Asset description</th>      <td>{{ asset.description }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Amount</th>                 <td class="amount">{{ asset.amount_human }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>USD value at time of theft</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</td></tr>
  {% if asset.usd_value_current %}
  <tr><th>USD value (current estimate)</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_current }}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
  {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
  <tr><th>KYC requirement at acquisition</th><td>Yes — {{ issuer.short_name }} required full identity verification{% if issuer.kyc_minimum %} with minimum subscription of {{ issuer.kyc_minimum }}{% endif %}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

<h2>5. Identified Wallets</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Address</th>
    <th>Role</th>
    <th>Type</th>
    <th>Notes</th>
  </tr>
  {% for w in identified_wallets %}
  <tr class="{{ w.row_class }}">
    <td class="mono">{{ w.address }}</td>
    <td>{{ w.role }}</td>
    <td>{{ w.type }}</td>
    <td>{{ w.notes }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>

<h2>6. Recommended Actions</h2>

<h3>Immediate</h3>
<ol>
  <li>
    Issue a preservation request to {{ issuer.name }}
    ({{ issuer.contact_email }}). As issuer, {{ issuer.short_name }}
    holds protocol-level authority over redemption and is the only party
    in a position to technically halt the {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} position at
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>. A request
    originating from your office is materially more enforceable than a
    third-party request.
    {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
    {{ issuer.short_name }} required full KYC at original subscription;
    they hold identifying information for {{ victim.name }} on file.
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
  <li>
    Copy {{ issuer.secondary_party }}, who manages the underlying
    {{ issuer.secondary_role }} the wrapper represents. They are the
    secondary route if {{ issuer.short_name }}'s freeze mechanism is
    unavailable or contested.
  </li>
  {% endif %}
  <li>
    Confirm chain-of-custody preservation of this evidence package and
    any linked case files. Per-transaction raw chain state at the time
    of fetch is retained on our side and available on request.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3>Investigative (over the following 1–2 weeks)</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Issue legal process to {{ issuer.short_name }} for KYC records on
      any party attempting to redeem or transfer the position out of
      <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>.</li>
  <li>Issue legal process to any centralized exchange that receives
      onward transfers from the identified perpetrator wallets listed
      in Section 5.</li>
  {% if issuer.jurisdiction %}
  <li>Coordinate with the financial-supervisory authority in
      {{ issuer.jurisdiction }} regarding the issuer's obligations to
      cooperate with the freeze.</li>
  {% endif %}
</ol>

<h2>7. Service Providers Involved</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Service</th><th>Role</th><th>Why relevant</th><th>Suggested contact</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>{{ issuer.name }}</td>
    <td>Issuer of stolen {{ asset.symbol }} wrapper token</td>
    <td>Has protocol-level control over redemption; primary freeze target</td>
    <td>{{ issuer.contact_email }} (request escalation to compliance)</td>
  </tr>
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ issuer.secondary_party }}</td>
    <td>{{ issuer.secondary_role|capitalize }}</td>
    <td>Controls underlying strategy; secondary freeze route</td>
    <td>(public compliance channel)</td>
  </tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

<h2>8. Verification</h2>
<p>
  Every fact in this package is drawn from public Ethereum mainnet state
  and is independently verifiable. Each transaction listed in the timeline
  links to its Etherscan record. For each transaction we retain, on file:
  the raw transaction object, receipt, block header, fetch timestamp, and
  direct verification link.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Sources: Etherscan API v2 (transaction history); CoinGecko (historical
  pricing); our internal label database for entity attribution.
</p>

<h2>9. Investigator Attestation</h2>
<div class="signature-block">
  <p>
    I prepared this package on behalf of {{ victim.name }} from public
    Ethereum mainnet data fetched between {{ trace_started_at }} and
    {{ generated_at }} UTC. The transaction hashes, addresses, timestamps,
    and amounts set out in this brief are accurate to the best of my
    knowledge and were independently verified at the time of fetch.
  </p>
  <div class="signature-line"></div>
  <div class="signature-fields">
    <strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong> · {{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
    Date: __________________________
  </div>
</div>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ brief_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Strictly Confidential.</span> Intended only for the receiving agency.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
